            <description><![CDATA[<p><span><span><span><span><span><span>中国驻美国大使秦刚说，中国将在“不久的将来”进一步放松防疫措施，并迎接更多的国际旅客。</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>
<p><span><span><span><span><span><span>据彭博社报道，秦刚星期一（</span></span></span></span></span></span><span><span><span><span><span><span><span>12月12日</span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span><span><span><span><span><span>）在新闻平台</span></span></span></span></span></span><span><span><span><span><span><span><span>Semafor举办的活动上</span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span><span><span><span><span><span>说，“我们了解大家的关切，目前防疫政策正在逐渐放宽，我相信在不久的将来，相关措施将进一步放松，国际旅行将更加便利。”</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>
<p><span><span><span><span><span><span>他在被问及中国国内针对防疫措施的抗议是否让政府是感到压力时做出上述表示。</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>
<section id="imu"><div id="dfp-ad-imu1">
        
</div>


</section>
<p><span><span><span><span><span><span>他也说，“面对冠病病毒的威胁，中国政府采取了非常负责任的态度来保护人民的生命。我们的应对政策一直是动态的，而不只是僵化进行封控并要求人们足不出户。”</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>
<p><span><span><span><span><span><span>在中国开始全国范围内的防疫封控后，进出中国的航班数量急剧下降，</span></span></span></span></span></span><span><span><span><span><span><span><span>中国将近三年来的国际旅行几乎停止</span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span><span><span><span><span><span>。</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>
<p><span><span><span><span><span><span>两名美国官员于</span></span></span></span></span></span><span><span><span><span><span><span><span>12月11日至12日</span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span><span><span><span><span><span>访问了中国，为国务卿布林肯未来几周的访华做准备。这是自疫情爆发以来，最高级别美国官员的到访，标志着中国防控措施正在放宽。</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>

<div id="innity-in-post"></div>
<div id="dfp-ad-midarticlespecial">
        
</div>



<p><span><span><span><span><span><span>目前，入境中国需要进行</span></span></span></span></span></span><span><span><span><span><span><span><span>“5+3”隔离（五天集中隔离+三天居家隔离）。</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>
